EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to health care; appropriating money to establish a
Pediatric Stem Cell and Bone Marrow Transplant
Program in this State; requiring certain reports to the
Interim Finance Committee; requiring the authorization of
certain audits; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill appropriates money to the Alliance for Childhood Diseases, doing
2 business as the Cure 4 The Kids Foundation, to establish a Pediatric Stem Cell and
3 Bone Marrow Transplant Program in this State. Section 1 of this bill appropriates
4 money to the Cure 4 The Kids Foundation for: (1) the infrastructure and equipment
5 necessary to operate the program; and (2) the costs of applying for and obtaining
6 accreditation from the Foundation for the Accreditation of Cellular Therapy.
7 Section 2 of this bill appropriates money to the Cure 4 The Kids Foundation for the
8 costs of operating the program during its first 2 years of existence, including
9 staffing and administration costs. Section 3 of this bill requires the Cure 4 The Kids
10 Foundation to: (1) submit reports to the Interim Finance Committee concerning
11 expenditure of the money appropriated by sections 1 and 2; and (2) allow the
12 Legislative Auditor to audit the books and records of the Cure 4 The Kids
13 Foundation.
